reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks great and expensive, BUT….
reviews.reviewText: Love the look of this very reasonably priced coffee table. Was kind of a nightmare to assemble, as the directions are not as clear as they should be. After installing hinges wrong and re-doing it, it finally came together and looks great. Only downsides: can’t open/close hinged part with one hand, and it’s not super smooth, but it does seem sturdy. And, I worry the finish will get damaged from liquids or scratched when using for drinks/food plates on it (are we only peeps that eat dinner always in front of tv sitting on sofa??) so I went to hardware store to see if I could get glass cut to put on top, and was quoted $150!! Not gonna spend twice the cost of table to protect the top, so we will see how long this lasts and how it wears.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great mid century coffee table for a reasonable price.
reviews.reviewText: I needed a coffee table and I saw this one and read the reviews so I went for it. Overall, it's a nice piece. The finish seems a little fragile so use coasters and don't put anything with rough edges on it. If a big dog jumps up on this, it's all over. The pull-up table is okay but a touch wobbly. I really don't use that part of it but I do enjoy the storage. My only issue is that it's rather small once you get it set up. I'd love the table more if it was twice as long. Also, they should really pre-assemble this and just ship it so you screw the legs on it (I got a file cabinet like that so I know they can do it). Anyway, I really can't complain for the price. I gave it a lot of stars because I needed one and this works. Also, it showed up on my doorstep so I didn't have to go to the store, deal with salespeople, wait a month, schedule the delivery. It just showed up with Prime. I'd recommend and I'd get this again for another room. I hope this helps you make an informed decision.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great for the money
reviews.reviewText: Product is particle board with plastic veneer. That said, the assembly instructions were clear. The pieces fit well together. Came with extra pieces of hardware just in case. Is pretty. Hydraulics are plenty stiff but move easily. I put it together by myself. It took me 2+ hours but everything worked well. Comes with all necessary tools but if you have your own screw drivers and socket wrench set, that worked better. Nice storage. Legs are plastic. I will replace with wood and a bit liner (taller) if possible. Nice storage. Well worth the sale price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Budget friendly and Very Functional
reviews.reviewText: My wife and I love this table. We replaced an old homemade coffee table in our living room with this one, and we love it. We frequently eat dinner at the coffee table and watch tv, and this is perfect for that. The assembly was kind of time consuming, but very straightforward. My one issue with this is the overall height. It sits very low in general. For some that may be great, for others maybe not. It is nice to kick your feet up on and feels very sturdy. The space inside holds way more than you think, we have ours filled with board games and other things. Watch out for the sharp corners with pets or little ones!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great storage and WFH area
reviews.reviewText: We have a small 1 bedroom apartment so storage is key for us and this coffee table met all of our marks.The lift up desk area is perfect to house video games, controllers, random clutter you need but can’t find a place for etc. it has helped declutter our house a lot.The lift up desk is perfect for a cozy work from home setup when you don’t have room for an entire office.The assembly seemed pretty easy my partner put it together in about an hour maybe a little more. It shows using a drill in the video but I would just use a screw driver as the wood is very thin and could crack really easily.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Let me be clear i loveeee this coffee table and for the price i have no complaints. But for a future buyer:I had a hard time getting some of the screws to go in all the way, so I had to use an electric drill. The instructions were easy to follow otherwise.Keep in mind it is a coffee table so even though it lifts up it is still quite short. if you have a low couch then it’ll be perfect but my couch is higher up. It doesn’t really affect me much but just a heads up!Those are the only negatives, its easy to install if you can follow instructions. Its color is nearly identical to the one in the photo, its sturdy (I stood on it to hang up Christmas lights the other day), overall worth the money

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Cheap material, great look
reviews.reviewText: So the material itself is very cheap. Similar to IKEA furniture that doesn't last long, but I cannot complain because I did buy it cheap on Black Friday. The design and look is perfect but the legs are plastic and the table is not real wood. I wouldn't recommend spilling things or scratching it because it chips easily.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A Little Challenging to Assemble, but Worth It!
reviews.reviewText: I started assembling this one evening, and had to walk away from it because I was so frustrated LOL! I tackled it again the next morning, ended up having to take it partially apart because the directions and labeling are TERRIBLE - but it was all worth it! The table is sturdy and beautiful. Reducing one start because the rising mechanism is a little floppy and weak, even though I purchased this to raise my laptop for Zoom calls, I don't trust it to hold the weight.

reviews.reviewTitle: No malgastes tú dinero en éste producto de pésima calidad
reviews.reviewText: Es un producto de pésima calidad. Tiene un par de meses y ya se le hizo un agujero sin haberlo golpeado. No malgastes tú dinero. NO ES DE MADERA. ES DE MDF OSEA ASERRÍN. NO SIRVE PARA NADA!!!
Es facil de armar, buena calidad y buena resistencia.Lo malo: la caja llegó muy dañada y un par de piezas co golpes en las esquinas.

reviews.reviewTitle: Muy baja calidad para el precio
reviews.reviewText: Dice que es madera y es mentira, el empaque venía mal y está en mal estado, tiraron la caja si no lo devolvía, no vale para nada lo que pagué
